data.name: A report is a process that creates a file based on one or several queries against the database settings configured at the activity level. A report must be scheduled. The file format can be choosen and if need the a deposit path can be defined. A report can be also sent by email.

An activity is basically a conenction to specific database server and schema. You can attached to it, a deposit path, a name and a logo. when you create an activity, a role with the same name is created in background

An alert is a process that send an email if one or several queries return a non null result against the database settings configured at the activity level. An alert must be scheduled and email recipients have to be defined
